    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Novartis</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      AEE788 is an orally active, reversible, small-molecule, multi-targeted kinase inhibitor with
      potent inhibitory activity against ErbB and VEGF receptor family of tyrosine kinases. It has
      an IC50 of less than 100 nM against p-EGFR, p-ErbB2, and p-KDR (VEGFR2). This study will
      assess the safety, pharmacokinetic (PK)/pharmacodynamic (PD) profiles and clinical activity
      of AEE788 in advanced cancers.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
